
👽 test linux/amd64

[EXPERIMENTAL]

Authenticate to cloud providers using an identity defined in atmos.yaml.

USAGE


    $ atmos auth login [flags]


FLAGS

  -h, --help             help for login

  -p, --provider string  Provider name to authenticate with (for SSO auto-provisioning)

      --tags string      Select an identity by tags (comma-separated, matches any): --tags=production,admin

      --webflow          Force a fresh browser login for an aws/user identity



Use --help=usage for examples or --help=all for all flags and full help.
